<item>
  <title>Mocking in Python</title>
  <dc:creator>Ivan Ogasawara</dc:creator>
  <link>https://example.com/posts/mocking-python/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>A mock is a controlled replacement for something your code normally uses.</p>
<p>In Python, we often use mocks in tests. Instead of letting the code talk to a real database, call a real web API, send a real email, or read a real file, we replace that dependency with a small object or function that behaves in a predictable way.</p>
<p>Mocks are useful because they let us test one piece of code at a time. The goal is not to test the internet, a third-party API, or a database server. The goal is to check whether our own function behaves correctly when it receives a certain response.</p>
<section id="when-to-use-a-mock" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="when-to-use-a-mock">When to Use a Mock</h2>
<p>Use a mock when the real dependency is:</p>
<ul>
<li>Slow, such as a network request.</li>
<li>Unstable, such as an external API that may be temporarily unavailable.</li>
<li>Expensive, such as a paid service.</li>
<li>Dangerous, such as code that sends emails, writes files, or changes production data.</li>
<li>Hard to reproduce, such as an API error or timeout.</li>
</ul>
<p>Mocks are especially helpful when a test should always produce the same result. If a test depends on a live website, it may pass today and fail tomorrow even when your code did not change.</p>
</section>
<section id="when-not-to-use-a-mock" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="when-not-to-use-a-mock">When Not to Use a Mock</h2>
<p>Do not mock everything. If a function is simple and does not depend on an external system, it is usually better to test it directly.</p>
<p>For example, a function that calculates a total price does not need a mock:</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> total_price(price, quantity):</span>
<span id="cb1-2">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> price <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">*</span> quantity</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Mocks are most useful at the boundary between your code and something outside your code.</p>
</section>
<section id="example-a-function-that-calls-an-api" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="example-a-function-that-calls-an-api">Example: A Function That Calls an API</h2>
<p>Imagine we have this function. It calls an API with <code>requests.get</code>, reads the JSON response, and returns the user’s name:</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb2" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb2-1"><span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">import</span> requests</span>
<span id="cb2-2"></span>
<span id="cb2-3"></span>
<span id="cb2-4"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> get_user_name(user_id):</span>
<span id="cb2-5">    url <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> <span class="ss" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">f"https://api.example.com/users/</span><span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">{</span>user_id<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">}</span><span class="ss" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"</span></span>
<span id="cb2-6">    response <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> requests.get(url, timeout<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span><span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">5</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-7">    response.raise_for_status()</span>
<span id="cb2-8">    data <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> response.json()</span>
<span id="cb2-9">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> data[<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"name"</span>]</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Testing this function against the real API would make the test depend on the network. The API might be down, the user might not exist anymore, or the response might change.</p>
<p>Instead, we can replace <code>requests.get</code> with our own function during the test.</p>
</section>
<section id="creating-a-mock-response" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="creating-a-mock-response">Creating a Mock Response</h2>
<p>The real <code>requests.get</code> returns a response object. Our function only needs two methods from that object:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>raise_for_status()</code></li>
<li><code>json()</code></li>
</ul>
<p>So our mock response only needs to implement those two methods:</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb3" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb3-1"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">class</span> MockResponse:</span>
<span id="cb3-2">    <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> <span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">__init__</span>(<span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>, json_data, status_code<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span><span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">200</span>):</span>
<span id="cb3-3">        <span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>.json_data <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> json_data</span>
<span id="cb3-4">        <span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>.status_code <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> status_code</span>
<span id="cb3-5"></span>
<span id="cb3-6">    <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> json(<span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>):</span>
<span id="cb3-7">        <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> <span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>.json_data</span>
<span id="cb3-8"></span>
<span id="cb3-9">    <span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> raise_for_status(<span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>):</span>
<span id="cb3-10">        <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">if</span> <span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span>.status_code <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">&gt;=</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">400</span>:</span>
<span id="cb3-11">            <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">raise</span> <span class="pp" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">Exception</span>(<span class="ss" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">f"HTTP error: </span><span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">{</span><span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">self</span><span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">.</span>status_code<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">}</span><span class="ss" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"</span>)</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Now we can create a mock version of <code>requests.get</code>:</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb4" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb4-1"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> mock_requests_get(url, timeout<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span><span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">None</span>):</span>
<span id="cb4-2">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> MockResponse({<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"id"</span>: <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">1</span>, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"name"</span>: <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"Ada Lovelace"</span>})</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>This function accepts <code>url</code> and <code>timeout</code> because the original code calls <code>requests.get(url, timeout=5)</code>. A mock should accept the arguments that the real function receives.</p>
</section>
<section id="activating-and-deactivating-the-mock" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="activating-and-deactivating-the-mock">Activating and Deactivating the Mock</h2>
<p>One simple way to activate a mock is to temporarily replace <code>requests.get</code>.</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb5" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb5-1"><span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">import</span> requests</span>
<span id="cb5-2"></span>
<span id="cb5-3"></span>
<span id="cb5-4">original_requests_get <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> requests.get</span>
<span id="cb5-5"></span>
<span id="cb5-6"></span>
<span id="cb5-7"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> activate_requests_get_mock():</span>
<span id="cb5-8">    requests.get <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> mock_requests_get</span>
<span id="cb5-9"></span>
<span id="cb5-10"></span>
<span id="cb5-11"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-weight: bold;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> deactivate_requests_get_mock():</span>
<span id="cb5-12">    requests.get <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> original_requests_get</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>After <code>activate_requests_get_mock()</code> runs, any code that calls <code>requests.get</code> will call <code>mock_requests_get</code> instead.</p>
<p>After <code>deactivate_requests_get_mock()</code> runs, <code>requests.get</code> is restored to its original behavior.</p>
</section>
<section id="using-the-mock-in-a-test" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="using-the-mock-in-a-test">Using the Mock in a Test</h2>
<p>Here is the full example:</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb6" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb6-1"><span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">import</span> requests</span>
<span id="cb6-2"></span>
<span id="cb6-3"></span>
<span id="cb6-4"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
